# $Id$

This test attempts to characterize the performance of the TRANSPORT_LATENCY
Quality of Service policy values.  See the Perl POD description embedded
in the run_test.pl script in this directory for additional information
about executing the tests.  Access this information most easily by
executing:

> ./run_test.pl --man

which will format the POD as a manual page on the terminal.

TEST SCENARIOS:

  Factors to consider include:
    Message Priority
    Message size and statistics
      Mean size
      Maximum size
      Minimum size
      Size distribution and parameters
        (Gaussian: average/variance)
    Message rate and statistics
      Mean rate
      Rate distribution and parameters
        (Poisson: average)
    Number of hosts
    Number of publication processes
    Publications per process
    Transport type

1) TCP, 1 Host, 2 publication processes, 2 publications per process
   process[12]/publication1:
     priority:            10
     max message size:  1200 bytes
     min message size:   800 bytes
     message statistics:
       size:     gaussian/average==1000;deviation==150
       interval: exponential/rate==100
   process[12]/publication2:
     priority:          ---unspecified (0)---
     max message size:  1200 bytes
     min message size:   800 bytes
     message statistics:
       size:     gaussian/average==1000;deviation==150
       interval: exponential/rate==100

